Capparis spinosa

   [4159.jpg]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Capparales:Capparidaceae
   Synonyms Capparis aegyptia Lam., Capparis spinosa var. aegyptia Boiss.,
   Capparis baducca Blanco, Capparis spinosa var. mariana Schumann,
   Capparis cartilaginea Decne., Capparis spinosa var. galeata Hook.f. &
   Thomson, Capparis galeata Fresen, Capparis mariana Jacq., Capparis
   ovata Desf., Capparis rupestris
   Common names caper, caper bush, caper berry, câpres, fabagelle, tapana,
   câprier commun, câprier épineux, câprier, alcaparra, caparra,
   alcaparrón, akbaar, kabbar, achalfah, assaf, asef, ward al jabal,
   shafallah, lasaf, terloulout, taybult, amserlih, tsailih, tsailaoul,
   ouai lonlou, belachem, lussef, alcaparras, cappero, cappero dei muri,
   cappero spinoso, capperone, Kapernstrauch, Kaper, echter Kapernstrauch,
   kappara, kappers, kappertjes, kapricserje, kaporna, kapribogyó, kebere,
   keber fidani, gebere, gebre otu, kapari, kapris, káppari, kapers,
   kapersy, torkav, kappar, kaporo, tzalaf, kiari, kobra, kabra,
   mullukattari, melada, kabarra, himsra, kokilakshmu, kabar, mruko,
   mchezo
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 4159

   Notes
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial shrub.
   COMMON NAMES
   Caper.
   FURTHER INF
   The caper bush can attain a height of about 1.5 m.

   Sources
   [10]Grassland Index
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 382 [TEMP, RAIN, DRA, TEXT, FER, USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 10 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Rhem S 1991 pp 287 [USE]

